energy is less than the band

00:37:46.491 --> 00:37:47.100
gap.

00:37:47.100 --> 00:37:49.180
And the second
major loss mechanism

00:37:49.180 --> 00:37:51.960
is when we have too much
energy of the incoming photon,

00:37:51.960 --> 00:37:54.340
we have an excitation
of a bound electron

00:37:54.340 --> 00:37:56.670
into a very highly
unbound state,

00:37:56.670 --> 00:38:00.890
and then a quick loss of that
excess energy due to a process

00:38:00.890 --> 00:38:03.490
called thermalization.

00:38:03.490 --> 00:38:05.791
Any questions so far?

